cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

The paper discusses Bayesian deep learning models for computer vision tasks, specifically semantic segmentation and depth regression. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses uncertainty modeling, which is a common topic in machine learning and deep learning, leading to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper introduces new loss functions, which could fall under the sub-category cs.SD (Sound).
